content:
Annotate Data Points with Tooltips and Markers

Create your own tooltips and markers in charts to show details about data points. Create a tooltip to specify which details appear when you hover over any data point.

Edit the dashboard and select the chart widget.
To configure the tooltip text, data point details, and visualizations, expand the Tooltip section of the widget properties.

Specify these tooltip details:
Add custom text: Specify your own text. To insert the value of a field in the text, click Add field.
Customize data point details: Show measures or dimensions in the tooltip, enable this option.
Show dimensions: Show the values of all selected dimensions.
Show measures: Show the values of all selected measures.
Show percentage: Show each measure’s percentage of the total.
Show null values: Show null values in the tooltips.
Add visualization: To add a chart, table, or a component that houses multiple widgets to the tooltip.

To add a marker for a data point, expand the Chart Markers section in the widget properties, and then click Edit Chart Markers. 

Select a data point in the chart where you want to add a marker.
Enter the following marker details:
Show dimensions: Show the values of all selected dimensions.
Show measures: Show the values of all selected measures.
Add custom text: Specify your own text. To insert the value of a field in the text, click Add field.
Open by default: Opens the marker and shows its text, by default.
Blink when closed: Makes the marker blink when it’s closed.
Background: Background color of the marker.
Border: Border color of the marker.

Preview the changes. Save the dashboard.
title: Annotating Data Points in Salesforce Analytics
